109 and the struck plant has so much power 110 that it impregnates the air with its virtue, 111 and that air, in turn, as it circulates, scatters it around;
112 and the other earth, according to its worthiness 113 in itself and in its climate, conceives and produces 114 different kinds of trees with different virtues.
